<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC, EURATOM) No 2728/94 of 31 October 1994 establishing a Guarantee Fund for external actions </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 2728/94 v&auml;listegevuse tagatisfondi asutamise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> 31. oktoober 1994 EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 235 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 235, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Atomic Energy Community, and in particular Article 203 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Aatomienergia&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 203, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Court of Auditors (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse kontrollikoja arvamust, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the general budget of the European Communities is exposed to increased financial risk as a result of the guarantees covering loans to third countries; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarve on vastuv&otilde;tlik lisanduvatele finantsriskidele, mis tuleneb kolmandate riikide laenudele antud tagatistest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Council on 11 and 12 December 1992 concluded that considerations of prudent budgetary management and financial discipline called for the establishment of a new financial mechanism, and that accordingly a Guarantee Fund should be set up in order to cover the risks related to loans and guarantees covering loans granted to third countries or for projects executed in third countries; whereas it is possible to meet this need by the establishment of a Guarantee Fund which may be drawn on to pay the Community's creditors direct; </inglise>
<eesti> 11. ja 12. detsembril 1992 j&otilde;udis Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu j&auml;reldusele, et eelarve usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse haldamise ja finantsdistsipliiniga seotud kaalutlused r&auml;&auml;givad selle kasuks, et asutada uus finantsmehhanism, mist&otilde;ttu tuleks asutada tagatisfond, mis kataks kolmandatele riikidele antud laenude ja laenutagatistega ning kolmandates riikides l&auml;biviidavate projektidega seotud riskid; seda vajadust rahuldaks fondi asutamine, mis maksaks otse &uuml;henduse v&otilde;lausaldajatele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the institutions have agreed, pursuant to the Interinstitutional Agreement of 29 October 1993, to enter into the budget a reserve relating to lending and guarantee operations for the benefit of and in third countries; </inglise>
<eesti> institutsioonid on 29. oktoobri 1993. aasta institutsioonidevahelise kokkuleppe kohaselt n&otilde;ustunud kandma eelarvesse reservi laenu- ja tagatistoimingute jaoks, mis tehakse kolmandate riikide kasuks ja kolmandates riikides; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas mechanisms currently exist for honouring guarantees when they are activated, in particular by drawing provisionally on cash resources, as provided for in Article 12 of Council Regulation (EEC, Euratom) No 1552/89 of 29 May 1989 implementing Decision 88/376/EEC, Euratom on the system of the Communities' own resources (4); </inglise>
<eesti> praegu on olemas mehhanismid tagatiste maksmiseks, eriti sularahavaru ajutiseks kasutamiseks, nagu on s&auml;testatud n&otilde;ukogu 29. mai 1989. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 1552/89 artiklis 12, millega rakendatakse otsust 88/376/EM&Uuml;, Euratom &uuml;henduste omavahendite s&uuml;steemi kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Guarantee Fund should be constituted by the gradual payment of resources; whereas the Fund will subsequently also receive interest on its invested resources and amounts recovered from defaulting debtors where the Fund has already honoured the guarantee; </inglise>
<eesti> tagatisfond asutataks j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult makstavatest maksetest; tagatisfond saab hiljem intressi investeeritud vahenditelt ja summadelt, mis saadakse laenukohustusi mittet&auml;itvatelt v&otilde;lgnikelt, kelle eest tagatisfond on juba tagatise maksnud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by reference to the practice of international financial institutions, a ratio of 10 % between the Guarantee Fund's resources and guaranteed liabilities in principal, increased by unpaid interest due, would seem adequate; </inglise>
<eesti> toetudes rahvusvaheliste rahaasutuste praktikale peetakse tagatisfondi vahendite ja tagatud kohustuste p&otilde;hisumma (mida on suurendatud tasumata intressi v&otilde;rra) sobivaks suhteks 10%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas payments to the Guarantee Fund equal to 14 % of the amount of each operation would seem appropriate to attain this target amount; whereas the arrangements for making such payments must be defined; </inglise>
<eesti> maksed tagatisfondi, mis on 14% iga toimingu summast, tunduvad olevat kohased soovitud summa saavutamiseks; tuleb m&auml;&auml;ratleda nende maksete tegemise kord; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, once the target amount is attained, the provisioning rate will be reviewed, whereas if the Guarantee Fund exceeds the target amount the surplus will be paid back to the general budget of the European Communities; </inglise>
<eesti> kui soovitud summa on saavutatud, vaadatakse toimingu protsendim&auml;&auml;r uuesti l&auml;bi ja kui tagatisfond on saanud soovitud summast rohkem raha, makstakse &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;k Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarvesse tagasi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the financial management of the Guarantee Fund should be entrusted to the European Investment Bank (EIB); whereas the financial management of the Fund should be subject to audit by the Court of Auditors in accordance with procedures to be agreed upon by the Court of Auditors, the Commission and the European Investment Bank; Whereas the Treaties do not provide any powers other than those pursuant to Article 235 of the EC Treaty and Article 203 of the EAEC Treaty for the adoption of this Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> tagatisfondi finantshaldamine tuleks usaldada Euroopa Investeerimispangale (EIP); kontrollikoja, komisjoni ja Euroopa Investeerimispanga vahelises kokkuleppes etten&auml;htud korra kohaselt kontrollib tagatisfondi finantshaldamist kontrollikoda; asutamislepingutes ei n&auml;hta k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks ette muid volitusi peale E&Uuml; asutamislepingu artiklis 235 ja Euroopa Aatomienergia&uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artiklis 203 s&auml;testatud volituste, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> A Guarantee Fund, hereinafter referred to as 'Fund', shall be established, whose resources shall be used to repay the Community's creditors in the event of default by the beneficiary of a loan granted or guaranteed by the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutatakse tagatisfond (edaspidi fond), mille vahendeid kasutatakse &uuml;henduse v&otilde;lausaldajatele tagasimaksmiseks, kui laenu saaja ei ole &uuml;henduse antud v&otilde;i tagatud laenu tagasi maksnud. </eesti>
<inglise> The lending and guarantee operations referred to in the first paragraph, hereinafter referred to as 'operations', shall be those carried out for the benefit of a third country or for the purpose of financing projects in third countries. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;ikes nimetatud laenamise ja tagamise toimingud (edaspidi toimingud) on toimingud, mida tehakse kolmandate riikide kasuks v&otilde;i kolmandates riikides l&auml;biviidavate projektide rahastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The Fund shall be endowed by: </inglise>
<eesti> Fondi rahastatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> - payments from the general budget of the European Communities pursuant to Article 4, </inglise>
<eesti> - Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarvesse artikli 4 kohaselt makstud maksetest, </eesti>
<inglise> - interest on Fund resources invested, </inglise>
<eesti> - fondi investeeritud vahendite intressist, </eesti>
<inglise> - amounts recovered from defaulting debtors where the Fund has already honoured the guarantee. </inglise>
<eesti> - summadest, mis saadakse laenukohustusi mittet&auml;itvatelt v&otilde;lgnikelt, kelle eest fond on juba tagatise maksnud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The Fund shall rise to an appropriate level, hereinafter referred to as 'the target amount'. </inglise>
<eesti> Fondi vahendid peavad j&otilde;udma eesm&auml;rgip&auml;rasele tasemele (edaspidi sihtsumma). </eesti>
<inglise> The target amount shall be 10 % of the Community's total outstanding capital liabilities arising from each operation, increased by unpaid interest due. </inglise>
<eesti> Sihtsumma on 10% iga toiminguga seotud &uuml;henduse kohustuste kogusummast p&otilde;hikapitali osas, millele lisandub tasumisele kuuluv maksmata intress. </eesti>
<inglise> If, at the end of a year, the target amount is exceeded, the surplus shall be paid back to a special heading in the statement of revenue in the general budget of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui aasta l&otilde;pus on soovitud summa &uuml;letatud, makstakse &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;k Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarve tulutabeli erirubriiki tagasi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The payments provided for under the first indent of Article 2 shall be equivalent to 14 % of the capital value of the operations until the Fund reaches the target amount. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 2 esimeses taandes etten&auml;htud maksed on 14% toimingute p&otilde;hisummast, kuni fond saavutab sihtsumma. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisioning rate shall be reviewed when the Fund reaches its target amount, and in any case no later than the end of 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> Makse protsendim&auml;&auml;r vaadatakse uuesti l&auml;bi, kui fond saavutab oma sihtsumma, kuid hiljemalt 1999. aasta l&otilde;pus. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Payments into the Fund shall be made in accordance with the arrangements indicated in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Maksed fondi tehakse vastavalt korrale, mis on esitatud lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> If, as a result of the activation of guarantees following default, resources in the Fund stand below 75 % of the target amount, the rate of provisioning on new operations shall be raised to 15 % until the target amount has once more been reached or, if the default occurs before the target amount is reached, until the amount drawn under the activation of the guarantee has been fully restored. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui lepinguliste kohustuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisele j&auml;rgnenud tagatiste kasutamise ajal on fondis v&auml;hem raha kui 75% sihtsummast, t&otilde;stetakse uute toimingute makse protsendim&auml;&auml;r 15%ni, kuni saavutatakse taas sihtsumma, v&otilde;i kui lepingulised kohustused on j&auml;etud t&auml;itmata enne sihtsumma saavutamist, kuni tagatise kasutamiseks v&auml;ljav&otilde;etud summa on t&auml;ielikult tagastatud. </eesti>
<inglise> If, as a result of the activation of guarantees on one or more major defaults, resources in the Fund fall below 50 % of the target amount, the Commission shall submit a report on exceptional measures that might be required to replenish the Fund. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme lepingulise kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisele j&auml;rgnenud tagatiste kasutamise ajal on fondi vahendid langenud alla 50% sihtsummast, esitab komisjon aruande erakorralistest meetmetest, mida v&otilde;idakse v&otilde;tta fondi vahendite t&auml;iendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall entrust the financial management of the Fund to the EIB under a brief on the Community's behalf. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon usaldab fondi finantshaldamise EIPle &uuml;hendusest saadud volituse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall, by no later than 31 March of the following financial year, send to the European Parliament, the Council and the Court of Auditors an annual report on the situation of the Fund and the management thereof in the previous year. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon saadab hiljemalt j&auml;rgmise finantsaasta 31. m&auml;rtsiks Euroopa Parlamendile, n&otilde;ukogule ja kontrollikojale fondi eelmise aasta finants- ja juhtimisaruande. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> The revenue and expenditure account and the balance sheet relating to the Fund shall be attached to the Communities' revenue and expenditure account and balance sheet. </inglise>
<eesti> Fondi tulude ja kulude aruanne ja bilanss lisatakse &uuml;henduste tulude ja kulude aruandele ja bilansile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall, before 31 December 1998, submit a comprehensive report on the functioning of the Fund. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab enne 31. detsembrit 1998 &uuml;ksikasjaliku aruande fondi tegevuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
